  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "- from what I understand, to `await` expect, `chai` needs an extra plugin: https://www.chaijs.com/plugins/chai-as-promised/\r\n- however, e.g. the hardhat docs https://hardhat.org/tutorial/testing-contracts show how to test with `await expect` without explicitly using chai-as-promised\r\n\r\n```\r\nawait expect(\r\n        hardhatToken.connect(addr1).transfer(owner.address, 1)\r\n      ).to.be.revertedWith(\"Not enough tokens\");\r\n```\r\n\r\ninstead, only chai's expect is required\r\n\r\n```\r\nconst { expect } = require(\"chai\");\r\n```\r\n\r\nIs this a mistake in the documentation or is hardhat monkeypatching chai? Or does chai now implement awaitable `expect`?",
